description.narrative: 2019 was a critical year to ensure that Clean India Mission (SBM) continues beyond its programmed end in October 2019. UNICEF (1) updated the 10 year rural sanitation strategy, (2) developed content of the ODF-Sustainability and ODF (FSM, SLWM) programmes, generated robust evidence which was used by the sector to request a further budgetary allocation of $ 12.5 billion for rural sanitation by 2024, fostered strategic partnership and led a large scale capacity development campaign to reach all 250,000 GPs of India. Over 18 million people received access to Household toilets for the first time in UNICEF supported districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/02/2020
